efill, repeat</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggxlA9yu8Ki_text","label":"ggxlA9yu8Ki_text","default":"<p>🔄 Breaks breeding cycle</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLZcXMX6k5_text","label":"ggLZcXMX6k5_text","default":"<p><strong>Yes</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggr_8WPnKpy_text","label":"ggr_8WPnKpy_text","default":"<p>No</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggw2w3N-eII_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggw2w3N-eII_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/1_eefc826a-957e-404a-b654-149d41b0bfc6.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggw2w3N-eII_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggw2w3N-eII_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/1_eefc826a-957e-404a-b654-149d41b0bfc6.png"},{"type":"html","id":"gg-Cauij223_text","label":"gg-Cauij223_text","default":"1. IT ACTUALLY ATTRACTS FLIES — NOT JUST THE ONES THAT BUMP INTO IT"},{"type":"html","id":"ggYUk5TKg6T_text","label":"ggYUk5TKg6T_text","default":"<p>That bug zapper crackling on your porch all night? It's killing moths and beetles. Flies barely register UV light.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sticky strips just hang there and hope. On a good day they'll catch three.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FlyDrop uses a natural bait formula that flies are biologically wired to seek out. They don't wander in by accident — they hunt it down.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Within minutes of adding water, you'll see them lining up to get inside.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>A trap that waits for flies is a decoration. A trap that hunts them is FlyDrop.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggP7R6itM3S_label","label":"ggP7R6itM3S_label","default":"<p>GET FLYDROP TODAY — LIMITED STOCK</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggKm2choVeg_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggKm2choVeg_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/2_fd9c0c47-73fe-48a5-9f82-65d09a7e3ac8.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggKm2choVeg_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggKm2choVeg_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/2_fd9c0c47-73fe-48a5-9f82-65d09a7e3ac8.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLYNAtoDXT_text","label":"ggLYNAtoDXT_text","default":"2. STOP THE BREEDING CYCLE — NOT JUST TODAY'S FLIES"},{"type":"html","id":"ggHq-I221c9_text","label":"ggHq-I221c9_text","default":"<p>Here's why it feels like a losing battle: a single female fly lays up to 500 eggs in her lifetime.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Most traps only deal with the flies you can see right now. Meanwhile, the ones you missed are laying hundreds of eggs in your trash, your compost, your horse's manure.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FlyDrop pulls flies away from breeding zones before they can reproduce. Once inside, they drown. No escape. No eggs. No next generation.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The longer it stays active, the fewer flies you'll have. Not because you're keeping up — because you're getting ahead.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Every fly you catch today is a thousand you won't deal with next week.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggQlR2PkH7s_label","label":"ggQlR2PkH7s_label","default":"<p>GET FLYDROP TODAY — LIMITED STOCK</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggEszb4LYf1_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggEszb4LYf1_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/3_42facf6d-defd-4166-bfaf-208443d76747.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggEszb4LYf1_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggEszb4LYf1_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/3_42facf6d-defd-4166-bfaf-208443d76747.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggDW2zDFZbd_text","label":"ggDW2zDFZbd_text","default":"3. SAFE AROUND YOUR ANIMALS, YOUR KIDS, AND EVERYTHING YOU WANT ALIVE"},{"type":"html","id":"ggEzcZVFfze_text","label":"ggEzcZVFfze_text","default":"<p>Read the fine print on chemical traps.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>\"Keep away from children and pets.\" \"Do not use near food.\" \"Wash hands after contact.\"</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Now think about where fly problems actually happen. The dog bowl. The chicken coop. The patio table where your kids eat lunch. The horse trough.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FlyDrop uses a natural bait attractant. No pesticides. No toxic residue. No chemicals near the things you're trying to protect.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>If the instructions say \"keep away from living things,\" maybe don't use it in a place full of living things.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGCMPLvPed_label","label":"ggGCMPLvPed_label","default":"<p>GET FLYDROP TODAY — LIMITED STOCK</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggrkRmZ-VrF_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggrkRmZ-VrF_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/4_dd34a3a8-888b-49fa-affd-d2d4bd8bbeaf.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggrkRmZ-VrF_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggrkRmZ-VrF_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/4_dd34a3a8-888b-49fa-affd-d2d4bd8bbeaf.png"},{"type":"html","id":"gghEsO2iE2v_text","label":"gghEsO2iE2v_text","default":"4. ONE TRAP. THOUSANDS OF FLIES."},{"type":"html","id":"ggfP0Acm1mh_text","label":"ggfP0Acm1mh_text","default":"<p>Let's compare what you're actually getting.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sticky strips catch maybe 20-30 flies and they're done. Generic bag traps leak at the seams half the time. Most store-bought options need replacing every few days.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FlyDrop catches thousands. Per trap.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Horse owners near barns fill a bag in days. Suburban homeowners go weeks watching it pack tighter and tighter. One customer said: \"I had no idea there were that many flies in my yard.\"</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>A trap that catches dozens is a hobby. A trap that catches thousands is a solution.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gghk7Kwk6lM_label","label":"gghk7Kwk6lM_label","default":"<p>GET FLYDROP TODAY — LIMITED STOCK</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggpOFENessJ_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggpOFENessJ_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/5_402b0d2c-9a82-4533-8da4-ebef44699170.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggpOFENessJ_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggpOFENessJ_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/5_402b0d2c-9a82-4533-8da4-ebef44699170.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPBZRcqDyK_text","label":"ggPBZRcqDyK_text","default":"5. TWO-MINUTE SETUP. NEVER TOUCH A DEAD FLY."},{"type":"html","id":"ggVeUm1sjW9_text","label":"ggVeUm1sjW9_text","default":"<p>Zappers need outlets and extension cords.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reusable traps need to be scrubbed out by hand — elbow-deep in dead fly slurry every time they fill up.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FlyDrop? Open the bag. Add water. Hang it. Done.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>No tools. No batteries. No refills. No cleaning. When it's full, throw it in the trash. You never touch the contents. Ever.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>If your fly trap takes more effort than the flies themselves, it's not a solution — it's a chore.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggO9eC_E95H_label","label":"ggO9eC_E95H_label","default":"<p>GET FLYDROP TODAY — LIMITED STOCK →</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg8go7zFMrq_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg8go7zFMrq_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/6_1219c7ed-5666-49f0-b302-3fd333affdf7.png"},{"type":"html","id":"gg8go7zFMrq_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"gg8go7zFMrq_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/6_1219c7ed-5666-49f0-b302-3fd333affdf7.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggjB97-n4xi_text","label":"ggjB97-n4xi_text","default":"6. BUILT FOR REAL OUTDOORS — NOT A LAB"},{"type":"html","id":"ggb32hUIq_l_text","label":"ggb32hUIq_l_text","default":"<p>Most traps weren't designed for real conditions.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Bait dries out in direct sun. Plastic warps in the heat. Sticky strips melt and drip. Bag seams split the second it hits 90 degrees.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FlyDrop was built for ranches in Arizona, farms in Alabama, and backyards in Texas where summer starts in April.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>It holds water in extreme heat. The bait stays active for weeks. It handles wind, rain, and sun that destroy generic alternatives in days.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Lab conditions don't have horse manure and 100-degree heat. Real properties do.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggt3nz5fbsQ_label","label":"ggt3nz5fbsQ_label","default":"<p>GET FLYDROP TODAY — LIMITED STOCK</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6FRGKhBFF_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg6FRGKhBFF_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/7.png"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6FRGKhBFF_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"gg6FRGKhBFF_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0748/4774/8295/files/7.png"},{"type":"html","id":"gg9kyeINfZ6_text","label":"gg9kyeINfZ6_text","default":"7. 2,000+ FIVE-STAR REVIEWS FROM PEOPLE WHO TRIED EVERYTHING ELSE"},{"type":"html","id":"ggjJ7CbgeQV_text","label":"ggjJ7CbgeQV_text","default":"<p>This is the part we can't write ourselves.</p><p>Two thousand verified customers. Horse owners. Chicken keepers. Suburban families who couldn't eat outside without swatting every ten seconds.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>They all tried sprays, strips, and zappers first. They all say the same thing:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i>\"I wish I'd found this sooner.\"</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FlyDrop isn't popular because of marketing. It's popular because people who use it tell their neighbors. And then their neighbors tell theirs.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>When 2,000+ people who've tried everything say this is the one — you don't need our word for it.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggQr4QToGof_label","label":"ggQr4QToGof_label","default":"<p>GET FLYDROP TODAY — LIMITED STOCK →</p>"}],
